  "title": "Shipping Administrator",
  "description": "<ol><li>Handle full set of import documentation including airway bills (AWB), invoices, packing lists, import permits, and customs documents.</li><li>Perform order processing, permit declaration, payment, and shipping documentation accurately and in a timely manner.</li><li>Liaise with internal departments and external stakeholders for the storage, transportation, and depot coordination of cargo.</li><li>Coordinate with relevant parties for the pick-up and shipment of cargo, ensuring smooth and timely delivery.</li><li>Generate and provide reports such as customer reports, import/export reports, and shipment status updates to Management.</li><li>Check all shipping documents for accuracy and ensure proper system input and data entry for final billing.</li><li>Track and follow up on incoming shipments (airfreight/seafreight) to avoid delays.</li><li>Work closely with authorities (e.g., Customs, MAQIS, DVS) to ensure compliance with all regulatory requirements.</li><li>Maintain proper filing and record-keeping for audit and traceability purposes.</li><li>Undertake any ad-hoc tasks assigned by superior or top management.</li></ol>",
